news.title: Asian Paints profit falls 18.5% to Rs 1,031.29 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: The company had posted a net profit of Rs 1,265.35 crore during the October-December quarter of the previous fiscal, Asian Paints said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Court upholds Bengaluru development body rule, dismisses site allottee's appeal
news.para: Latha was allotted site no. 589 under Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes quota, the total value of which was Rs 7,58,500. She gave Rs 3.65 lakh on August 24, 2006, and Rs 1 lakh on October 11, 2006. She did not pay the remaining amount in time.

news.title: Bank takes over Nava Raipur development body's property after loan default
news.para: Union Bank of India’s mid-corporate branch issued a public notice in newspapers on taking symbolic possession of 2.659-hectare land of NRDA after issuing a demand notice on August 2 last year, seeking repayment within two months.

news.title: Lucknow development body to sell plots near international stadium
news.para: According to LDA officials, the development authority is selling plots ranging from 10,000 square metres to 27,000 square metres in the Central Business District (CBD) located at Shaheed Path. All these plots are meant for commercial purposes.

news.title: Bengaluru: Landlords face six police cases over illegal layouts in Varthur
news.para: According to police, the suspects developed residential layouts without getting land-use conversion approved from the department concerned and without obtaining permission from competent authorities to develop layouts.

news.title: Task Force, Hyderabad development body officials pull down 10 more illegal buildings
news.para: Five such structures were pulled down in Thumukunta area, two in Manikonda, two in Shamshabad and one in Pedda Amberpet limits. Officials said that out of the demolished structures, two of them were spread over an area of 2.25 acres in Thumukunta and another big one covering an area of 1.2 acres in Shamshabad.

news.title: Kerala: Order issued to cancel 530 illegal land titles
news.para: The land titles were issued by the then deputy tahsildar M I Raveendran, who was holding the charge of additional tahasildar in Devikulam, in 1999, by overstepping his powers.

news.title: Court order refusing relief to Ansals in Uphaar case not perverse: Delhi HC told
news.para: Special public prosecutor (SPP) Dayan Krishnan urged Justice Subramonium Prasad, who was hearing petitions by the Ansal brothers and another convicted person Anoop Singh Karayat for suspension of the seven-year sentence, to not interfere with the trial court orders.

news.title: Gurugram: 10 illegal commercial units along Golf Course Road sealed
news.para: Recently, deputy commissioner Yash Garg, during a district task force meeting, had directed the town planner of enforcement wing of town and country planning department to carry out sealing drive in Saraswati Kunj area.

news.title: Hiranandani, Blackstone joint venture plans Rs 3,000 crore investment
news.para: The joint platform is looking to build and expand its portfolio by at least 15 million sq ft, taking it to more than 20 million sq ft in the next five years.

news.title: China drafts rules to ease property developers' use of escrow funds: Sources
news.para: Years of regulatory curbs on borrowing via typical channels has plunged the sector into a deep crisis, highlighted last year by the troubles at China Evergrande Group - once the country's top-selling developer and now the world's most indebted property company with $300 billion in liabilities.

news.title: How will government rehabilitate the displaced, Kerala HC asks
news.para: Considering six petitions filed by tribals involved in the Chengara land struggle for allotment of land, Justice Devan Ramachandran pointed out that the state government had entered into an agreement with them in 2001 to allot lands.

news.title: Home builder sentiment dips in U.S. in January 2022
news.para: The reports supported views that the economy started the year on a soft note because of high inflation, shortages and raging coronavirus cases, driven by the Omicron variant.

news.title: Over 4,000 online applications for land allotment received by J&K industries department
news.para: It was informed at a meeting chaired by J&K Chief Secretary Arun Kumar Mehta to review the functioning of the industries and commerce department here, the spokesman said.

news.title: Third wave could take 100-200 bps off HFCs' asset growth: Crisil
news.para: Growth would still be higher compared with average of about 2% over fiscals 2020 and 2021 though slower than the broad-based 24% logged between fiscals 2011 and 2019, with a near two-fold increase in the number of HFCs over that decade, fuelled by easy availability of equity and debt capital.
